
cohesion: how well the parts inside one class belong together
(we want)high cohesion - one class has one clear job

coupling: how much one class depends on other classes
(we want)low coupling - classes are less tightly connected

dependency inversion principle (dip)
: high-level modules(control logic) should not depend on low-level modules(details)
both should depend on abstractions

separation of concerns (soc)
: split the system into parts where each part handles one concern

single responsibility principle (srp)
: a class should have one main responsibility, so it has one primary reason to change

Q&A
1.Vilka beroenden är nödvändiga?

inheritance: volvo,saab,scania -> car
- they share common car state and behavior
realization(implements): car -> movable, flak -> liftable
- needed because movement is a core contract for all cars
- needed because flak behavior is defined by that interface
composition(has): scania -> flak
- the bed logic is part of scania's core behavior
carcontroller and carview
- according to MVC, to send commands and get updates

2. Vilka klasser är beroende av varandra som inte borde vara det?
3. Finns det starkare beroenden än nödvändigt?

CarController depends on concrete class(scania, saab, workshop, drawpanel)
instead of abstractions. DIP warning!!

those fixed value of car/workshop width and height
- only work on these specific pictures
- we should instead generelize

4. På vilka klasser skulle ni behöva tillämpa dekomposition för att bättre följa SoC och SRP?
- CarController: it currently has multiple responsibilities and many reasons to change
split into parts CollisionLogic (wall/workskop collision), WorkshopService (load/unload rules)
